  "text": "Better Place originally focused on Israel, where they planned a large network of charging and 9 swapping stations to cover the entire nation by 2012. This plan included 2.5 charging spots for every car 10 on the road in Israel, starting with 500,000 charges, in total costing between $50 and $100 million 11 [CITATION_1] . At the same time, Better Place did not restrict its operations only to Israel and 12 soon expanded to Denmark, with plans to expand to Australia, China, and the United States. Better 13 Place partnered with Renault, and their joint battery swap-capable car was the Renault Fluence Z.E. 1 ",
